BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:R4IstspKZdAOOjII2aThO
SUMMARY:Decay
DTSTAMP:20260409T031208Z
DTSTART:20260410T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Decay explores how we navigate and engage with the inevitable e
	ntropy of our world.\n\nThis exhibition shows us the joy of degeneration\,
	 the beauty of collapse\, the peace that comes from crumbling into dust. T
	he work\, primarily from Pacific Northwest artists\, ranges from sculptura
	l\, to wall-mounted 3D\, video and installation works. Included in this ex
	hibition will be works created using natural and reclaimed materials\, as 
	well as pieces designed to create spaces for quiet reflection on the theme
	. Decay appears as part of the natural world and in our bodies in many for
	ms\, and so over the duration of the show\, some works may change over tim
	e\, exemplifying the theme. Many of the pieces prompt reflection on mortal
	ity\, the fragility of the physical body and the sacred.\n\nhttps://seatod
	ay.6amcity.com/events/#/details/decay/18493748/2026-04-10T00\n\nFrom SEAto
	day - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/decay/18493748/2026-04-10
	T00
LOCATION:The Vestibule\, 5919 15th Ave. N.W.\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT5H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:iAD5TTiwM-eJmHrTx9Lw0
SUMMARY:Scott Gibson - Visual Symphony II
DTSTAMP:20260409T031208Z
DTSTART:20260410T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:In March\, Visual Symphony II Scott Gibson invites viewers into
	 a world where music and art collide. Each work is an exploration of the v
	ivid\, sensory experience of sound translating into vibrant\, emotional vi
	suals. As an artist with synesthesia each work expresses Scott’s personal 
	perception of what music looks like. Scott uses resin techniques that he h
	as pioneered and pushes the boundaries of this medium.\n\nhttps://seatoday
	.6amcity.com/events/#/details/scott-gibson-visual-symphony-ii/18280602/202
	6-04-10T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/scott-gibson-visual-symph
	ony-ii/18280602/2026-04-10T00
LOCATION:Gray Sky Gallery\, 320 First Ave. S.\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT4H
END:VEVENT
