BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:iZbPRdbLf1_hMNCkfOjPb
SUMMARY:Samantha Yun Wall: What We Leave Behind
DTSTAMP:20260409T031208Z
DTSTART:20260411T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Samantha Yun Wall’s new paintings use overlapping silhouettes o
	f female figures as portals to unknown spaces and different temporal realm
	s. Impetus for the new body of work is a Korean folk tale in which the Pas
	que flower is symbolic of a grandmother who passed away without the loving
	 care of her grandchildren. It is a story of melancholy\, loss\, and remem
	brance. The delicate hair on the flower’s stem differentiates it\, and the
	 artist gives the plant a surreal aspect in some of her paintings\, replac
	ing the flower’s center with a watchful eye.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.c
	om/events/#/details/samantha-yun-wall-what-we-leave-behind/18026187/2026-0
	4-11T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/samantha-yun-wall-what-we
	-leave-behind/18026187/2026-04-11T00
LOCATION:Seattle Art Museum\, 1300 First Avenue\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:1Gg5stewLoMY0WJkw4STm
SUMMARY:Family Saturday | Get Ready for Baby Rave
DTSTAMP:20260409T031208Z
DTSTART:20260411T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Gear up for Baby Rave by transforming everyday items into vibra
	nt wearable works of art with guidance from teaching artist\, Claudia Vill
	alobos! Upcycle materials including cardboard\, fabric scraps\, and repurp
	osed embellishments to design wings\, crowns\, skirts and other wearable p
	ieces that sparkle\, reflect light\, and show off your family's creativity
	. Ideal for kids and grown-ups to create together. Then spend your afterno
	on with your family exploring art and the natural environment. This progra
	m takes place outside at the Olympic Sculpture Park on the covered north t
	errace of the PACCAR Pavilion. Walk-ins welcome on a first-come\, first-se
	rved basis.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/family-saturd
	ay-get-ready-for-baby-rave/18529076/2026-04-11T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Sport
